{#
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  COMPONENT: Empty State
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Consistent empty-state block for empty lists, no-data screens, etc.
  Much more professional than plain text "Keine Einträge".

  Parameters:
    icon    (html,   optional) — raw SVG icon html (centered, 24px usually)
    title   (string, optional) — headline ("Noch keine Patienten")
    text    (string, optional) — body copy
    cta     (html,   optional) — raw button html for call-to-action

  Usage:
    {% include 'components/_empty-state.twig' with {
        icon:  '<svg width="24" height="24">…</svg>',
        title: 'Noch keine Patienten',
        text:  'Lege deinen ersten Patienten an, um loszulegen.',
        cta:   '<a href="/patienten/neu" class="btn btn-primary">Patient anlegen</a>'
    } %}
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
<div class="tp-empty-state">
    {% if icon is defined %}
    <div class="tp-empty-state-icon">{{ icon|raw }}</div>
    {% endif %}
    {% if title is defined %}
    <div class="tp-empty-state-title">{{ title }}</div>
    {% endif %}
    {% if text is defined %}
    <div class="tp-empty-state-text">{{ text }}</div>
    {% endif %}
    {% if cta is defined %}
    {{ cta|raw }}
    {% endif %}
</div>
